ADL Delivers Signatures Calling on Rex Tillerson to Appoint Anti-Semitism Envoy

By Red Ice -   2 days ago 1 212 




Share on Facebook
Tweet on Twitter






Editor’s note: it is significant that the office of Special Envoy to Monitor and Combat Anti-Semitism has remained vacant during the Trump presidency. It is possible that Trump’s administration is incrementally distancing itself from the Israel Lobby and likeminded organizations.
The Anti-Defamation League (ADL) today delivered to the U.S. State Department thousands of signatures on a petition calling on President Trump and Secretary of State Rex Tillerson to fill the vacant office of Special Envoy to Monitor and Combat Anti-Semitism as quickly as possible.
The envoy position, mandated by the Anti-Semitism Awareness Act signed into law by President George W. Bush in 2004, has remained vacant since the beginning of the Trump administration. Secretary of State Tillerson indicated in testimony before Congress in June that the administration had yet to make a decision about whether the position would be filled at all.
The ADL petition urges Mr. Tillerson to appoint a Special Envoy immediately to continue an office that “has served as an invaluable diplomatic and domestic purpose in fighting anti-Semitism” under Democratic and Republican administrations alike.
“We know firsthand that this role is critical to fighting anti-Semitism and it is vital that the United States continue to manifest its leadership in fighting hate around the world,” said Jonathan A. Greenblatt, ADL CEO. “And we are not alone. Thousands of Americans have signed our petition urging the…

